# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# geometric-learning.form — symmetry as data: one gather operator
# carries convolution, message passing, diffusion, and embedding
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The teaching arrived via the field 2026-06-10 (Geometric Deep
# Learning, shared by @probnstat — x.com/probnstat/status/
# 2064807526005461480): learning extends beyond Euclidean grids to
# graphs, manifolds, and meshes by respecting symmetry — invariance
# and equivariance are the inductive biases, convolution generalizes
# to geometric operators, and CNNs are the special case the lattice
# gets for free. The post's diagram is f: Graph → ℝⁿ — a graph
# embedded into a manifold.
#
# The Form answer is the core-abstraction move: the domain enters as
# DATA — a list of (i j w) edge triples — and ONE engine walks every
# domain. No grid path, no graph path, no mesh path. SHIPPED:
# `form/form-stdlib/geometric-learning.fk` +
# `tests/geometric-learning-band.fk` → 8388607 (23 claims), three-way
# (Go/Rust/TS).
#
# The engine is SEMIRING-GENERIC — (combine, weigh) arrive as data,
# carrier-proven (defn names pass as values, params dispatch in verb
# position, identical three-way):
#
#     gl-gstep:  y_i = ⊕_{(i j w)} w ⊗ x_j      — the geometric operator
#     gl-step    = gl-gstep with (add, mul)      — sum-product reading
#     gl-bellman = gl-gstep with (max, r+γ·v)    — max-plus reading
#     gl-diffuse: gl-step iterated               — heat flow on the domain
#     gl-mean:    global pooling                 — the invariant readout
#     gl-embed:   diffuse a seed, deflate mean   — f: Graph → ℝ, the
#                                                  diffusion-map coordinate
#
# Readings of the same operator, decided by edge data and semiring alone:
#
#   Euclidean convolution   gl-ring-edges: circulant weights — the
#                           weight depends only on the offset, which IS
#                           translation symmetry visible as data symmetry
#   graph message passing   gl-mesh-edges: symmetric uniform kernel +
#                           lazy self-loops over an undirected pair list
#   diffusion               a row-stochastic kernel makes gl-step a
#                           heat step; mass conserved, the constant
#                           mode is the invariant the flow settles into
#   manifold embedding      power iteration by diffusion + constant-mode
#                           deflation — the dominant surviving mode is
#                           the domain's community/chart coordinate
#   morphological dilation  the SAME ring edges under (max, +) — one
#                           edge list, two semirings
#
# The three limbs the post names — "a unifying framework linking ML,
# DL, and RL" — are instances, not new machinery:
#
#   ML   gl-gnn-layer / gl-gnn-readout — a GNN layer whose weights
#        (ws wn b) are recipe data; neighbor aggregation IS gl-step
#        over pair edges. The readout is a graph invariant: a molecule's
#        predicted property survives relabeling, while structure (same
#        atoms, different bonds) still discriminates — the symmetry that
#        makes GNNs right for chemistry, checked.
#   DL   gl-radius-edges — point clouds: the graph is built FROM
#        geometry (pairwise distance), so edges — and everything
#        downstream — are rigid-motion invariant (E(2)). Heat diffused
#        through built edges stays chart-bounded: zero leakage between
#        disconnected clusters, exactly.
#   RL   gl-bellman / gl-value-iterate — relational planning: value
#        propagates from the goal through graph-structured states to
#        the optimal fixed point; the backup is permutation-equivariant
#        (agents/states interchangeable). Planning is diffusion's
#        tropical twin — the same gather under (max, +).
#
#   gl-attn-edges (composes transformer-numerics' tn-softmax) builds
#   data-dependent edges: attention IS gl-step on the complete graph.
#   The band proves the rows are stochastic (constants pass through),
#   a silent query attends uniformly (attention degenerates to
#   diffusion), and the output carries the input's mirror antisymmetry.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What the band proves (each a falsifiable claim, not an assertion)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The core claims ride two strange-minimal domains:
#   · the 4-ring — the periodic 1-D Euclidean grid; kernel [.25 .5 .25]
#     and x = [8 4 0 4] keep every value exact in binary floats
#   · the triangular prism K3×K2 — a 3-regular mesh with two charts
#     (two triangles bridged by rungs); its second diffusion mode IS
#     the chart split (eigenvalue 2/3 vs 1/2), so power iteration
#     separates the charts provably fast
# The limb claims add: a 4-state relational world with an absorbing
# goal (γ = ½, dyadic rewards — the fixed point is exact), a 5-point
# two-cluster cloud (dyadic positions and kernels — leakage is exactly
# zero), two 3-atom molecules sharing the same atom multiset (path vs
# triangle), and attention over x = [1 0 −1].
#
#   1     conv([8 4 0 4]) = [6 4 2 4]            — the CNN form lands
#   2     gl-step(circulant) ≡ gl-conv           — CNNs ARE geometric
#                                                  operators on lattices
#   4     conv(shift x) = shift(conv x)          — translation equivariance
#   8     gl-step(π·edges, π·x) = π·gl-step(edges, x)
#                                                — permutation equivariance;
#                                                  π = swap(0,1) is NOT an
#                                                  automorphism: the theorem
#                                                  is about transporting
#                                                  structure with signal
#   16    mean(π·y) = mean(y)                    — invariant readout
#   32    sum(diffuse(x,3)) = 16 exactly         — mass conservation
#   64    diffuse(x,3) = [4.5 4 3.5 4] exactly   — smoothing
#   128   diffuse(x,24) = [4 4 4 4] at 1e-6      — convergence to the
#                                                  invariant (constant mode)
#   256   embed signs (+ + + − − −)              — the two charts separate
#   512   embed[0] = 7805 at 1e-6                — pinned to the IEEE fp64
#   1024  embed[4] = −7154 at 1e-6                 oracle, fold-order exact
#   2048  embed[1]=embed[2], embed[4]=embed[5]   — the embedding recovers
#                                                  the mesh's mirror symmetry
#                                                  through the seed
#   4096  (max,+) over the same ring edges       — morphological dilation
#         = [8.5 8.25 4.25 8.25]                   one edge list, two semirings
#   8192  value iteration → V* = [3 4 4 0]       — RL: value propagates from
#                                                  the goal through relations
#   16384 bellman(V*) = V*                       — the optimum is a fixed point
#   32768 backup permutation-equivariant         — relational symmetry
#   65536 radius graph rigid-motion invariant    — rotate 90° + translate:
#                                                  identical edge list (E(2))
#   131072 chart-bounded diffusion               — far cluster exactly 0;
#                                                  in-cluster [118652 98877 98877]
#   262144 molecular property graph-invariant    — relabeled → 4666667 both ways
#   524288 structure discriminates               — same atoms, different bonds
#                                                  → 5666667 ≠ 4666667
#   1048576 attention rows stochastic            — constants pass through
#   2097152 silent query attends uniformly       — attention output 0 at the
#                                                  zero-feature node
#   4194304 attention mirror antisymmetry        — out[2] = −out[0], out[0]
#                                                  = 575210 at 1e-6
#
# The conformance discipline is form-native-models': compute in fp64,
# reduce to integers at 1e-6, pin to a reference that mirrors the
# recipe's exact fold order. Determinism is the feature — every kernel
# computes the same bits.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Kinship
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   form-native-models.form     the sequence/Euclidean lane (transformer
#                               numerics, M1–M6). gl-attn-edges proves the
#                               kinship at toy scale: softmax(x_i·x_j)
#                               builds the (i j w) list and THE SAME
#                               gl-step consumes it — the transformer is
#                               a GDL instance; the two lanes are one
#                               teaching. This module preludes
#                               transformer-numerics.fk for tn-softmax.
#   ml-diffusion-model-flow.form  denoising diffusion — the generative
#                               reverse flow in latent space. This module
#                               is diffusion ON a domain (heat flow), the
#                               operator GDL generalizes convolution from.
#                               Two readings of "diffusion learning,"
#                               both now native.
#   attention.fk                the QKV walk this module's operator view
#                               re-grounds structurally.
#   mesh-relay.fk / mesh-gradient.fk  the body's own mesh tissue — the
#                               next occurrence of a hot neighborhood-
#                               aggregate wants gl-step, not a sibling.
#   metabolic-learning.form     the learner that moves this body: the
#                               satsang operator (pressure × frequency ×
#                               angle × focus) as mtb-step over the same
#                               edge data — a zero learner arrives at
#                               this module's proven CNN exactly, and
#                               tunes its own focus dial recursively.
#
# The LEARNING-the-weights stone is walked: metabolic-learning.form —
# the satsang operator as the training loop over this engine (the
# gradient reading; champion-challenger remains its discrete sibling).
# Next stones when an ask needs them (named, not built ahead of need):
# vector node features (the dot in gl-attn-edges and the weights in
# gl-gnn-layer grow into M1/M2's tensor stones); irregular-degree walks
# (1/dᵢ weights — the prism's 3-regularity let uniform and walk kernels
# coincide).
